The paper focuses on learning sparse representations for multimodal data, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. The paper also discusses the use of joint dictionary learning and deep architectures, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper demonstrates the effectiveness of the proposed approach in classification tasks, which is a common problem in natural language processing (cs.CL).
